<p>The max angle should be &lt;= +135. Sometimes it is good to make it a little less for safety.<br>
The min angle is just negative max angle.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>gear ratio</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yea my examples were bad LOL</p>
<p>Basically the gear ratio is how many times the encoder spins a full rotation for the turret rotates around once.</p>
<p>So what you can do is move the turret some degrees, well say N.</p>
<p>Now convert that degrees to rotations by dividing by 360, that gives us R. (R = N/360)</p>
<p>Then you take the amount of rotations the encoder spun, we can say E.</p>
<p>Gear Ratio = E / R</p>
<pre><code class="lang-plaintext">Example:

we spin the turret 180° and the encoder spins 10 times

N = 180 and E = 10

R = N / 360 = 180 / 360 = 0.5

Gear Ratio = E / R = 10 / 0.5 = 20

Then your gear ratio is 20. 
</code></pre>
